# Check: Code Quality

Run the code quality dimension sub-checks. This ensures code meets linting, complexity, and naming standards.

## Sub-checks

1. **Lint** — Run the project linter
   - See: [check_d_linter.mdc](check_d_linter.mdc)
   - Script: `scripts/run-lint.sh`

2. **Complexity** — Check function length, nesting depth, cyclomatic complexity
   - See: [check_v_code_complexity.mdc](check_v_code_complexity.mdc)
   - Script: `scripts/verify-code-quality.sh`

3. **Naming** — Verify naming conventions follow language/project standards
   - Script: `scripts/verify-naming-conventions.sh` (to be implemented)

## Instructions

1. Run `scripts/run-lint.sh <feature_dir>` — no lint errors
2. Run `scripts/verify-code-quality.sh <feature_dir>` — complexity within thresholds
3. Run `scripts/verify-naming-conventions.sh <feature_dir>` — naming conventions followed
4. If any sub-check fails:
   - Fix lint errors (automatically fixable ones first)
   - Refactor complex functions (split, reduce nesting)
   - Rename non-conforming identifiers
5. Record results in `.artifacts/check-results/`

## Gate Criteria

- **Critical tier**: ALL sub-checks must pass.
- Linter: zero errors (warnings allowed with suppression comments)
- Complexity: per thresholds in `scripts/code-quality-thresholds.sh`
- Naming: follow established project conventions
